  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nPerf test OOM quite frequently. I haven't been able to take a heap snapshot so I'm still on the black.\r\n\r\nLatest time in CI it happened here, right after the `badcase_full_deposits` case\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/99369b137a3575b2edd6aeb31c35f2bc134a461a/packages/beacon-state-transition/test/perf/phase0/epoch/processRegistryUpdates.test.ts#L41\r\n\r\n```\r\n  phase0 processRegistryUpdates\r\n    ✓ phase0 processRegistryUpdates - 250000 normalcase                   12536.04 ops/s    79.77000 us/op   x0.283      76605 runs   14.0 s\r\n    ✓ phase0 processRegistryUpdates - 250000 badcase_full_deposits        187.7203 ops/s    5.327073 ms/op   x0.462         59 runs   6.85 s\r\n\r\n<--- Last few GCs --->\r\n\r\n[2269:0x4b76cd0]   824055 ms: Mark-sweep (reduce) 4093.3 (4101.6) -> 4092.5 (4102.9) MB, 4576.8 / 0.0 ms  (average mu = 0.070, current mu = 0.001) allocation failure scavenge might not succeed\r\n[2269:0x4b76cd0]   828392 ms: Mark-sweep (reduce) 4093.5 (4101.9) -> 4092.8 (4102.9) MB, 3798.6 / 0.0 ms  (average mu = 0.098, current mu = 0.124) allocation failure scavenge might not succeed\r\n\r\n\r\n<--- JS stacktrace --->\r\n\r\nFATAL ERROR: Ineffective mark-compacts near heap limit Allocation failed - JavaScript heap out of memory\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nNot OOM",
